00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:05,610
而这个舰队 还缺乏法律人才
And this fleet is not exactly brimming with legal talent.

166
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:09,700
如果你让律师介入 他们会把这次审判拖上几个月
You bring lawyers into this, they're gonna drag you around for months.

167
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:12,910
令尊不曾是卡布里卡的一名律师吗?
Wasn't your father an attorney on Caprica?

168
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,960
对 我也告诉过你 我与他相处得不太好
Yes. And I told you that I didn't get along with him very well.

169
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:17,540
好吧
Oh, right. Okay.

170
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:21,840
我准备建立一个组织委员会 不过坦率地说
I'm ready to set up an organizing committee, but frankly,

171
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:26,090
要让满屋的法律学者按章办事是强人所难
trying to get a room full of legal scholars to stay on task is like herding cats,

172
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:30,180
所以我要选拔一位委员会主席
and so I need to set up a chairman of this committee,

173
00:13:30,260 --> 00:13:31,810
一个可以做出艰难决策的人
somebody who can make a hard decision

174
00:13:31,890 --> 00:13:35,230
不会被法律术语控制或束缚的人
and who won't get seduced and bogged down by all the legalese.

175
00:13:35,310 --> 00:13:37,230
有合适人选了吗?      我倒是早有人选了
Do you have a candidate? As a matter of fact, I do.

176
00:13:37,310 --> 00:13:39,610
我认为李可以
I was thinking Lee.

177
00:13:39,690 --> 00:13:42,570
可能"有其爷爷  必有其孙子" 你认为呢?
Like grandfather, like grandson, perhaps. What do you think?

178
00:13:42,650 --> 00:13:44,990
不是我说他无法胜任
I'm not gonna say he's incapable of handling it,

179
00:13:45,070 --> 00:13:49,620
只是他从没显露过对法律有兴趣
but he's never shown any type of interest in law.

180
00:13:50,740 --> 00:13:52,490
我知道  但事情是这样
I know, but here's the thing.

181
00:13:52,580 --> 00:13:54,450
我们可以利用律师来剖析法律
We can use the lawyers to parse the law,

182
00:13:54,540 --> 00:13:56,910
但我们真正需要的是能够明辩是非曲直的人
but we really need people who actually know the difference

183
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:00,080
李就是这种人
between right and wrong. That's Lee.

184
00:14:00,170 --> 00:14:01,880
我会和他谈谈   好
I'll talk to him. Good.

185
00:14:03,090 --> 00:14:04,460
还有一件事  上将
Also, Admiral?

186
00:14:05,380 --> 00:14:10,180
今天我可以在你的船上度过吗?
I was wondering if you mind if I stayed on your ship for the rest of the day.

187
00:14:10,260 --> 00:14:12,600
当然可以
Please. By all means.

188
00:14:15,890 --> 00:14:19,350
我不太好意思说 就是…
This is very difficult for me to say, but

189
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,560
我要去健身房
I'm going to go to the gym.

190
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,860
你可要小心了  
Prepare yourself.

191
00:14:25,940 --> 00:14:28,610
人多的时候 里面有股臭鞋的味道
On its best days, it smells like the inside of a shoe.

192
00:14:38,250 --> 00:14:39,210
看看还有没要修补的
See if there's another patch in there.

193
00:14:39,290 --> 00:14:42,580
这里要双重加固
I want to double up on this one and make sure it holds.

194
00:14:42,670 --> 00:14:44,630
快  阿莉 早完事  
Come on, Cal. Faster is better. The sooner we do this,

195
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:48,760
早出去    我早听到了
the sooner we can get out of here. I heard you the first time.

196
00:15:01,850 --> 00:15:04,230
你越来越善于 无视这些周遭的事情了
CAROLANNE: You're getting better at ignoring all of that.

197
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:07,730
官兵们突然肃静  用眼角余光瞥你
That sudden hush, those sidelong glances.

198
00:15:07,820 --> 00:15:10,150
这些都曾让你很不安
That really used to get to you.

199
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:14,410
倒是想不起来这些能让你畏惧过
Don't ever recall being able to intimidate you.

200
00:15:14,490 --> 00:15:15,660
对
That's right.

201
00:15:15,740 --> 00:15:18,500
但早在你成为上将之前  我就已经认识你了
But I knew you long before you were the Admiral.

202
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:20,660
当你还只是比尔的时候
Back when you were just Bill.

203
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:23,960
抛妻弃子的那个人
My husband who wasn't there. The father who left.

204
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:25,670
只是比尔的时候
Just Bill.

205
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:28,920
谁是比尔・阿达玛?  这还是一个好问题
Who is Bill Adama, anyway? Still a good question.

206
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:31,720
我都不知道是否能得到答案
I wonder if I'll get an answer.

207
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:35,010
49天没有出现了
Forty-nine days without a sighting.

208
00:15:35,850 --> 00:15:38,390
看来真把"烤面包机"们吓跑了
Maybe we finally scared the toasters off.

209
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:42,890
对  纳卓  就你那烂技术把他们吓得心里有阴影了
Oh, yeah, Narcho. Your crap flying has put the fear of the Gods in them.

210
00:15:46,190 --> 00:15:47,860
你好吗  兄弟?
What's up, buddy?

211
00:15:55,530 --> 00:15:57,950
怎么了?
What's the matter with you?

212
00:15:58,040 --> 00:16:01,580
不好意思 我这里长了一片奇怪的红疹
Sorry. I've got the weirdest rash.

213
00:16:01,660 --> 00:16:02,870
真的?
Really?

214
00:16:03,670 --> 00:16:05,880
但愿她值得你这样  兄弟
Hope she was worth it, buddy.

215
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:13,680
起立!
Ten-hut.

216
00:16:19,560 --> 00:16:20,770
稍息
At ease.

217
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:28,440
在我们开始之前 我想做个调查
Before we get started, I want a show of hands.

218
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:31,070
你们这群傻蛋中有几个人会数数?
How many of you boneheads know how to count?

219
00:16:37,580 --> 00:16:41,080
因为机库中的数数声不绝于耳
Because I keep hearing numbers being thrown around the hangar deck.

220
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:43,460
47  然后是48...
Forty-seven, then 48,

221
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:46,670
自从我们最后一次发现敌人到现在  已有49天了
now 49 days since our last enemy contact.

222
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:50,670
我看得出再难一点的数学 你们中大部分人可能也不会
Now, I realize that any higher math is probably beyond most of you.

223
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:53,880
所以我就简单地说
So, I'm going to make this real simple for you.

224
00:16:57,140 --> 00:17:01,770
1是你们唯一需要记住的数字
One is the only number you need to remember.

225
00:17:01,850 --> 00:17:05,440
因为只要一名驾驶员疏忽大意
Because all it takes is for one pilot to let his guard down,

226
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:08,190
一名电子干扰员错过雷达上所出现的目标
one ECO to miss a dradis contact,

227
00:17:08,270 --> 00:17:11,150
而赛昂人就会突然出现在我们眼前了
and suddenly, the Cylons are on top of us.

228
00:17:13,110 --> 00:17:15,030
这时候就会死人
That's when people die.

229
00:17:16,610 --> 00:17:18,410
他像我们两个人一样
ADAMA: He's like both of us.

230
00:17:24,330 --> 00:17:26,620
高傲  顽固  愤怒
Proud, stubborn and angry.

231
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:32,300
可他已经可以独自决断了 尤其是近几个月以来
But he's coming into his own, especially in the last few months.

232
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,630
这事不要告诉我
CAROLANNE: Don't tell me.

233
00:17:36,380 --> 00:17:38,640
要告诉他   他知道
Tell him. He knows.

234
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:40,260
知道什么?
He knows what?

235
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:45,350
知道上将会说他有杰出表现?
That the Admiral's going to give him a good performance review?

236
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:48,020
或是他的父亲爱他?
Or that his father loves him?

237
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:53,150
别告诉我上将对李也要展现那一面
Don't tell me the Admiral's facade extends to Lee, too.

238
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:56,570
编队飞行
APOLLO: Formation flying,

239
00:17:56,650 --> 00:17:58,740
偏角射击 战术
deflection shooting, tactics,

240
00:17:58,820 --> 00:18:03,240
连续飞行 直到你们每个人三项都合格
doing touch-and-goes, until every last one of you hits an OK3.

241
00:18:03,330 --> 00:18:07,290
红队和蓝队先来 黄队和绿队随后开始
Red and blue sections will go first. Yellow and green will follow.

242
00:18:07,370 --> 00:18:09,540
10分钟内升空  解散
Skids up in 10 minutes. Dismissed!

243
00:18:24,470 --> 00:18:26,640
星芭 如果你有异议 我也不想听
Starbuck, if you've got a problem, I don't want to hear about it.

244
00:18:26,730 --> 00:18:27,850
嗯
Mmm!

245
00:18:28,270 --> 00:18:32,560
一周前你可没对我们如此严厉呀
My only problem is that you didn't preach that sermon a week ago.

246
00:18:32,650 --> 00:18:34,610
你最好换些花样
You might want to find some new material, though.

247
00:18:34,690 --> 00:18:37,860
自从我们来了这里 老头子一直在用"一个致命错误"这句话
The old man's been using that "one fatal mistake" line since we got here.

248
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:41,240
你要偷学别人的话 就要找最出色的人偷学
Well, if you're gonna steal, steal from the best.

249
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:45,540
长官
Sir.

250
00:18:50,710 --> 00:18:52,750
今天对他们挺严格的
Pretty tough on them today.

251
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:55,300
忠言逆耳
Well, a kick in the butt is worth a thousand words.

252
00:18:55,380 --> 00:18:57,800
您对我的管教就够严的
Gods know you kicked mine enough.

253
00:18:59,300 --> 00:19:00,680
一切都好吧?
Everything okay?

254
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:03,640
恩  和以前的几个早上一样
Yeah, it's been one of those mornings.

255
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:06,810
总统想快些审判波塔尔
The President wants to take the fast track on Baltar's trial.

256
00:19:06,890 --> 00:19:09,430
她想找一位可以主管准备工作的人
She's looking for someone to take charge of the preliminaries,

257
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:12,020
来把法律体制搭配起来
help cobble together the legal framework.

258
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:14,190
她想让我选派你
She wants me to assign you.

259
00:19:15,860 --> 00:19:17,400
说笑吧?
You're kidding.

260
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:20,570
有兴趣?
Interested?

261
00:19:21,070 --> 00:19:22,660
更多的是意外
More surprised.

262
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,330
她说了为什么选派我吗?
Did she say why she asked for me?

263
00:19:25,410 --> 00:19:28,580
她需要值得信赖的人选
Well, she's gonna need someone that she can trust.

264
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,870
你绝对符合这个标准
You definitely fit that.

265
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:38,710
我还记得你稍年轻的时候 去你祖父家
I remember when you were younger, you'd go visit your grandfather's house.

266
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:41,930
你对他的那些论文和法律书籍很痴迷
You were fascinated with his papers and his law books.

267
00:19:45,220 --> 00:19:48,140
我也想过 当时自己鬼鬼崇崇的样子
And there was me, thinking I was being sly,

268
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:51,390
独自一人潜入他的办公室
sneaking off into his office all by myself.

269
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:56,650
现在只是白日做梦了 但我在参军之前…
You know, I guess it's a pipe dream now, but for five minutes there,

270
00:19:56,730 --> 00:19:59,280
真的考虑过当律师
I really did consider "lawyer"

271
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:05,370
会是我未来的职业之一
as one of the dozen careers that I could go into before I joined the service.

272
00:20:07,120 --> 00:20:08,290
嗯
Hmm.

273
00:20:08,830 --> 00:20:10,500
这我倒不知道
I never knew that.

274
00:20:12,620 --> 00:20:17,960
应该是在"生爸爸气"那段时间
Well, it was probably during one of my "angry at Dad" phases.

275
00:20:20,460 --> 00:20:22,720
总之 这是不可能的
Anyway, it's impossible.

276
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:25,640
即使我想帮忙  也帮不上
Even if I wanted to help out, there's no way.

277
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:29,930
就算一周比较轻松  空军队长也要全天忙
CAG's duty's already 24/7, even on a light week.

278
00:20:30,850 --> 00:20:33,230
恩 我猜也是
Yeah. I assumed that.

279
00:20:33,310 --> 00:20:35,150
少校 我们准备好了
NARCHO: Major? We're ready for you.

280
00:20:35,770 --> 00:20:37,150
失陪了
Excuse me.

281
00:20:55,330 --> 00:20:57,630
反正都要试一下
Yeah, well, one's gonna have to do.

282
00:20:57,710 --> 00:21:00,170
希里克斯 检查一下压力 如果补丁能支撑住 
Seelix? Check the pressure. If that patch holds,

283
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:02,420
几分钟内压力就可以平衡 门就会打开了
we're gonna equalize in a few minutes. This door's gonna open.

284
00:21:02,510 --> 00:21:03,630
好
Okay.

285
00:21:10,510 --> 00:21:11,930
见鬼
Oh, my Gods.

286
00:21:25,530 --> 00:21:27,950
他们怎么样了?      还活着
How are they doing? Still alive.

287
00:21:29,330 --> 00:21:33,200
三级警报 14号甲板上出现船体裂口
WOMAN ON P.A.: This is a Condition 3 alert. Full breach on Deck 14.

288
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:39,380
轮机长
Chief.

289
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,630
上将...
Admiral?

290
00:21:42,710 --> 00:21:45,670
看来我已经造成了  无法挽回的损失
I seem to have turned this into a full-blown fubar.

291
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:50,140
如果您能把这道门打开  可真是帮了我们大忙
You'd be doing us a hell of a favor to get those doors open.

292
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:55,180
我们得把他们救出来
We gotta get them out of there.

293
00:21:56,850 --> 00:21:58,900
运动运动  运动运动
Keep moving. Keep moving.

294
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:12,240
过渡舱被设计为在舱压突然降低时就会关闭舱门
The airlock is designed to lock down if the pressure decreases unexpectedly.

295
00:22:12,330 --> 00:22:14,700
所以只要... 我了解这套系统
So, as soon as that patch... I know the system.

296
00:22:14,790 --> 00:22:17,330
我们还有其他办法  还有备用方案
We have redundancies, we have backups...

297
00:22:17,420 --> 00:22:19,540
手控超驰装置已经失灵
The manual override is down.

298
00:22:19,630 --> 00:22:22,920
无法打开内门
There is no way of getting those inner doors to open.

299
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,670
过渡舱一定是在逃出新卡布里卡的时候遭到了重击
The thing must have taken heavy damage on the way out of New Caprica.

300
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:26,840
整艘船都受到了重创
Whole ship's taken a pounding.

301
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:29,760
我们得在干船坞中呆上六周  来修补弹坑
We need six weeks in dry-dock just to hammer out the dings,

302
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:31,590
更别说还要处理结构损伤
let alone tackle the structural damage.

303
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:32,760
他们还有多少时间?
How much time do they have?

304
00:22:32,850 --> 00:22:36,890
以裂缝的尺寸来看 不到半小时 可能就会没有氧气
From a leak that size, they'll be out of air in half an hour, maybe less.

305
00:22:36,980 --> 00:22:41,520
那些是密闭门 至少要用一小时才能切开
Those are blast doors. It would take at least an hour to cut through them.

306
00:22:42,860 --> 00:22:45,280
为什么不在观察室里安置炸药?
TIGH: Why don't we put explosives in the observation booth?

307
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:46,530
把玻璃炸碎  拉他们出来
Blow the glass, pull them out...

308
00:22:46,610 --> 00:22:49,400
行不通 那面玻璃足以承受泰里恩爆炸
No, that glass is strong enough to withstand a tylium explosion.

309
00:22:49,490 --> 00:22:51,160
能把玻璃炸碎的话 
Anything strong enough to take out the glass

310
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:54,030
蒂罗尔和凯莉也活不了
will take out Tyrol and Cally at the same time.

311
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:56,370
我要的是一个营救计划
I need a rescue plan,

312
00:22:57,410 --> 00:22:59,080
不是诸多借口
not excuses.

313
00:23:14,220 --> 00:23:15,720
七秒钟
Seven seconds.

314
00:23:15,810 --> 00:23:19,060
因为这是在外太空作业 我们还需要10秒的增压时间
And another 10 to re-pressurize, since we'll be doing this in open space.

315
00:23:19,140 --> 00:23:20,890
难上加难
That's pushing it.

316
00:23:20,980 --> 00:23:22,520
我提这个问题可能很傻 
All right, this might be a stupid question,

317
00:23:22,610 --> 00:23:24,560
但有人尝试过这样的营救方法吗?
but has anyone ever tried a rescue like this before?

318
00:23:24,650 --> 00:23:25,900
还没有人这么疯狂过
No one has ever been crazy enough.

319
00:23:25,980 --> 00:23:28,440
管不了那么多了 我们没时间了  准备起飞
Doesn't matter. We're out of time. Prep for launch.

320
00:23:28,530 --> 00:23:29,900
只剩18分钟了
We've only got 18 minutes left.

321
00:23:29,990 --> 00:23:32,160
好  走吧 开始行动
All right, let's go. We're on.

322
00:24:12,490 --> 00:24:13,700
加伦
CALLY: Galen.

323
00:24:20,700 --> 00:24:22,910
过渡舱门还是卡在那里  轮机长
ADAMA: Airlock's still jammed, Chief.

324
00:24:23,540 --> 00:24:25,710
超驰控制也没有反应
Overrides are not responding.

325
00:24:28,340 --> 00:24:31,260
看来我们无计可施了
Guess we're kind of running out of options.

326
00:24:31,340 --> 00:24:34,340
我会派人从前门救你们出去
I'm gonna take you out through the front door.

327
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:40,890
你要派一艘船在外面...
You're going to put a ship out there,

328
00:24:40,980 --> 00:24:43,060
搭建一个浮坞环?
rig up some kind of docking collar?

329
00:24:43,140 --> 00:24:48,230
几分钟之内 你们的氧气就会耗尽  没有时间搭环
You'll be out of air in a few minutes. There's no time for a collar.

330
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:54,400
