503
00:39:14,350 --> 00:39:17,020
还说你想造一座小屋
Said you wanted to build a cabin.

504
00:39:17,100 --> 00:39:20,140
当时是波塔尔的奠基仪式
It was Baltar's groundbreaking ceremony.

505
00:39:21,600 --> 00:39:23,730
那天晚上  我有点没头没脑的
I got a little silly that night.

506
00:39:28,490 --> 00:39:32,200
你是否想过如果赛昂人没回来  又会发生什么事?
Do you ever wonder what would have happened if the Cylons hadn't come back?

507
00:39:32,280 --> 00:39:36,540
考虑到波塔尔和当地的地形  我们也无法离开那里
Well, I think, given Baltar and the terrain, we couldn't have made a go of it.

508
00:39:36,620 --> 00:39:39,200
你呢?  会留在卡拉狄加上?
What about you? Do you think you would have stayed on Galactica,

509
00:39:39,290 --> 00:39:41,330
还是会定居在新卡布里卡?
or do you think you would have settled?

510
00:39:41,420 --> 00:39:44,380
扯得太远了吧?
It's pretty hypothetical, isn't it?

511
00:39:45,300 --> 00:39:47,170
是远了 可为时不远了
It is, until it isn't.

512
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:54,720
瞧我刚才说的是什么话
Did I just say that?

513
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:57,310
能看到你这样笑 也算值得了
It was worth just seeing you laugh like that.

514
00:39:57,390 --> 00:40:01,270
战斗得太久 有时却忘了我们在为什么而战
We've been at war for so long, sometimes we forget what we're fighting for.

515
00:40:01,350 --> 00:40:03,810
静心地抚养子女
To raise our kids in peace.

516
00:40:03,900 --> 00:40:08,530
执子之手与子偕老 又可以享受正常的生活
Enjoy one another's company. Live life as people again.

517
00:40:08,610 --> 00:40:09,860
比如像在新卡布里卡上的那个晚上
Like that night on New Caprica.

518
00:40:09,940 --> 00:40:14,620
才是我们所真正向往的  对吧?
That's really what we are talking about here now, isn't it?

519
00:40:14,700 --> 00:40:17,620
那时候 还有其他一些时候都算是
That, and other times.

520
00:40:19,660 --> 00:40:22,290
那如果赛昂人没有回来的话?
So, if the Cylons hadn't come back...

521
00:40:26,210 --> 00:40:27,710
但他们还是回来了
But they did.

522
00:40:38,680 --> 00:40:41,140
我们有一定责任
We have certain responsibilities.

523
00:40:41,680 --> 00:40:44,270
是的  长官  另外…
Yes, we do, sir, and...

524
00:40:45,900 --> 00:40:47,690
我几天以后还会来
I will be back in a few days.

525
00:40:47,770 --> 00:40:52,610
如果你愿意 我们可以再好好聊聊那天晚上的事
And if you'd like, we can talk more about that night.

526
00:41:02,290 --> 00:41:03,410
比尔?
Bill?

527
00:41:05,130 --> 00:41:06,540
答案是肯定的
The answer is yes.

528
00:41:08,040 --> 00:41:10,590
我肯定会造那座小屋
I absolutely would have built the cabin.

529
00:41:19,350 --> 00:41:20,600
去吧
CAROLANNE: Go ahead.

530
00:41:21,310 --> 00:41:25,140
像每次结婚周年纪念日之后 你把它放起来一样
Put it away, like you have after every anniversary.

531
00:41:25,230 --> 00:41:27,150
答应我 你不会再把它翻出来
Promise me you won't take it out again.

532
00:41:27,230 --> 00:41:29,150
恨你或许更容易一些
ADAMA: Be easier to hate you.

533
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:34,400
可那就是在自欺欺人了 卡罗兰
But that would be a lie, Carolanne.

534
00:41:36,110 --> 00:41:38,950
这一辈子 我们之间的谎言已经够多了
And there's been enough of that through our lives.

535
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:50,210
我们还是有值得纪念的事情的吧?
We had something, didn't we?

536
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:54,880
恩 是有
Yeah. We had something.

537
00:42:06,980 --> 00:42:08,730
明年再见
See you next year.

